{"NIB":[{"def":"The bill or beak of a bird; the neb.","pos":""}],"NIBBED":[{"def":"Having a nib or point.","pos":""}],"NIBBLE":[{"def":"To bite by little at a time; to seize gently with the mouth; to eat slowly or in small bits.","pos":""}],"NIBBLER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, nibbles.","pos":""}],"NIBBLINGLY":[{"def":"In a nibbling manner; cautiously.","pos":""}],"NIBELUNGENLIED":[{"def":"A great medieval German epic of unknown authorship containing traditions which refer to the Burgundians at the time of Attila (called Etzel in the poem) and mythological elements pointing to heathen times.","pos":""}],"NIBELUNGS":[{"def":"In German mythology, the children of the mist, a race of dwarfs or demonic beings, the original possessors of the famous hoard and ring won by Siegfrid; also, the Burgundian kings in the Nibelungenlied.","pos":""}],"NIBLICK":[{"def":"A kind of golf stick used to lift the ball out of holes, ruts, etc.","pos":""}]}